properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 31 at 5:11AM AKST until February 1 at 6:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Cold wind chills to 55 below occurring. The cold wind
chills will cause frostbite in as little as 10 minutes to
exposed skin.

* WHERE...Central Beaufort Sea Coast.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM Saturday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds are expected to decrease this
evening and winds chills will become less severe, but
temperatures will remain very cold.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for cold wind chills means that very
cold air and sustained wind speeds of 15 mph or more will create
dangerously low wind chill values. Frost bite can occur quickly
and even hypothermia or death if precautions are not taken. The
latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM AKST SATURDAY
